President Trump made a speech in Missouri about tax cuts and reform. He argued that tax cuts would bring better-paying jobs to Main Street in America and make businesses more competitive. Cabinet members and elected officials, including Secretary of the Treasury Steven Mnuchin and Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue, expressed their support for tax reform. Republican lawmakers from Missouri also praised the President's efforts and expressed the need for tax relief. Media outlets reported on Trump's speech and highlighted his push for tax cuts and the potential impact on the economy.